The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Thursday, September 19, 2002 				 Hydrous hues
																								Great good is said to be like water,																								Sustaining life with no conscious striving,																								Flowing naturally, providing nourishment,																								Found even in places																								Which desiring man rejects.																								  Too-te-Tching																								Water  the very manifestation of Natures generosity. Soft, muted, yielding to touch, yet versatile, omnipresent and ever-potent  it manifests in its being the principles of Prana (life) and creativity. Vikalp Art Shop is currently hosting an exhibition of watercolours titled Hydrous Hues, showcasing works of renowned contemporary artists including Shanu Lahiri, Rabin Mondal, Isha Mohammed, Shyamal Dutta Roy, Sanat Kar, Ramananda Bandopadhyay, Suhas Roy, Jogen Chowdhury, Shuvaprasanna, Subrata Gangopadhyay, Pradip Maitra, Wasim R. Kapoor, Tapas Sarkar, Somnath Maity, Dilip Chaudhury, Saikat Bhattacharjee and others. Also, as tribute to the late artist Shaibal Ghosh, two of his watercolours have been mounted in this show. Watercolour was Ghoshs forte and he carried out several experiments with this medium. 																								When: Till September 22; 4 pm - 8 pm; 																								Where: Sabhaghar, Swabhumi, the Heritage Plaza
